name: Blaine Street Adult Clinic
review_text: I just wanted to adjust my rating of this place the Blaine Street adult clinic has been instrumental and influential in my life so of course it deserves five stars all of the people there in the clinicians and therapists are awesome. They offer multiple groups and tomorrow even though having pizza you know but I've also found in order to make any type of recovery or progress you have to find someone to hold you accountable you have to actually be accountable to yourself if you hold yourself accountable you can always see improvement but you won't actually make improvement and tell you have someone hold you accountable. Often times I've blamed others for not seeing the perception of things are potential in them and also once happiness can only be determined by one's self if you respond to another's actions with happiness or sadness they are in control of your emotions that would be insane so that's one good thing I've learned and also if you put in the time and the work and hold yourself accountable you always make improvements hope it's the first time also you should check out the groups and I don't know if I can actually mention any of the therapist my hand but they're all awesome everyone knows that thank you Blaine clinic and I'm sorry that I've always been in pain

name: Blaine Street Adult Clinic
review_text:
The first psychiatrist I had kept increasing my prescriptions at an alarming rate despite having no history of taking medications. To the point where I was getting physically ill and my mental health was not getting any better either. Despite saying that I was physically ill he increased my meds yet again and apparently was writing in his chart that I was improving and made no notes that I was getting ill.
I initially came to get therapy BEFORE deciding to take meds and was pressured into taking medication anyways. Its been SIX MONTHS and I have not seen a therapist beside an offsite one which I had to stop seeing bc she was straight up trying to diagnose me before even talking to me or evaluating me and I want a REAL diagnosis. I want to get BETTER and these people are seriously using me like a Guinea pig.

name: Blaine Street Adult Clinic
review_text: Im not happy at all with their services...  they dont care about the clients and they dont provide the proper help and needs of the clients. Sad that these people get paid so much and dont help the clients. Ive had enough of it. Im having to look somewhere else for my services since these people cant help me and do their job.

name: Blaine Street Adult Clinic
review_text: Peer Supporters needs retraining when dealing with Mental Illnesses and HIPPA Rights. Jeremiah Southworth tried to Terminate Services for family member, not his place or position to do so overstepping his duties,    A family member asking for help, Jonie three times no referrals for counseling. Ashley Gerhardt left messages for her about two - three weeks no response until we went to their Supervisor. Lisa in transportation discarded my family member HIPPA Rights when Lisa went in her leasing office to ask them for her phone number and address. Because Lisa in the field unprepared.

review_text: The staff is SO AMAZING! They are friendly and understanding. The make you feel welcome. And if you have to wait bring a foosball to play on their table.

name: Blaine Street Adult Clinic
review_text: I LOVE my psychiatrist Dr Amadore. I would refer anyone to him. I also have my G.P. In the same office. She is the best physician, Christine. I have ever had and I'm 57 years old so that says a lot. She is very thorough . The only complaint I would have would be the outside of the building. It always seems cluttered with homeless ppl and filthy. There was even human feces in front of the building. If I didn't like my doctors so much, that would deter me from going there.
